---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import QuoteBlock from '../components/QuoteBlock.astro';
import StatCard from '../components/StatCard.astro';
import CTABanner from '../components/CTABanner.astro';
---

<Layout title="ZoneMaintenance — Equipment Management International" description="ZoneMaintenance software streamlines mobile mining equipment maintenance with digital work instructions, reducing PM service times by 30% and breakdowns by 40%.">
  <Nav />
  <main id="top" class="pt-20">
    <!-- Hero -->
    <PageHero
      title="ZoneMaintenance Software"
      subtitle="Advanced and flexible mobile mining equipment maintenance software"
    >
      <div class="mt-4">
        <img src="/images/products/zone-maintenance-logo.jpg" alt="ZoneMaintenance logo" class="h-24 sm:h-32 rounded-lg" />
      </div>
    </PageHero>

    <!-- A Simple Repeatable Process -->
    <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-base-100">
      <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
          <div>
            <h2 class="section-heading mb-6">A Simple Repeatable Process</h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 prose-body">
              <p>
                Do you have declining fleet reliability or long turnaround servicing and repair times? Or is your maintenance team swamped in paper-based service sheets?
              </p>
              <p>
                Our powerful and innovative software options improve efficiency and safety — no matter the level of employee experience.
              </p>
              <p>
                ZoneMaintenance electronically sets out for a technician what needs to be done, when, and how. It also details requirements for tools, lubricant, parts and permits. Images, videos and PDFs can be used to support task steps. The system clearly identifies any risks involved and when contamination control needs to be applied.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-center">
            <img src="/images/products/zonemaintenance-ipad.jpg" alt="ZoneMaintenance iPad interface" class="rounded-xl shadow-lg max-w-sm w-full" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Beyond Digital Instructions -->
    <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-base-200">
      <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2 class="section-heading text-center mb-12">
          But We Take It Much Further Than Just Digital Instructions
        </h2>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
          {[
            'Defect recording with risk-rating for future repair priority',
            'Images of the defect can be captured',
            'Any previously reported or outstanding defects can easily be viewed and edited',
            'Technical prompts determine equipment condition',
            'Values outside the min/max range automatically trigger the defect reporting process',
            'Integration of Sensory-Based Data functionality',
            'Technicians can record what they see, hear, smell, and touch',
            'Simple to adopt and manage, user-friendly and designed to work with your workforce',
          ].map((feature) => (
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4">
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-primary flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
              <p class="text-base">{feature}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Common Site Problems -->
    <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-base-100">
      <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2 class="section-heading text-center mb-4">
          ZoneMaintenance Addresses Many Mobile Plant Issues
        </h2>
        <p class="prose-body text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-12">
          Research shows that many mining sites struggle with similar issues, particularly when it comes to mobile plant maintenance. Do any of these common site problems sound familiar?
        </p>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-3 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
          {[
            'Poor skill levels and competencies',
            'Poor quality repairs and servicing practices',
            'Poor defect identification & management',
            'Poor data collection methods',
            'Poor turnaround times of servicing and repairs',
            'Poor customer (operations) relationships',
            'Poor presentation of end product',
            'Poor process controls and management',
            'Poor resource management',
            'Poor identification of skills required',
            'Poor planning and scheduling methods',
            'Poor condition monitoring analysis',
            'Poor safety standards at task level',
            'Poor availability of information at task level',
            'Poor understanding of task purpose or procedures',
            'Over servicing and under servicing of equipment',
            'Loss of knowledge through high staff turnover',
            'High maintenance and management costs',
            'Poor equipment reliability and availability',
            'Lack of standards and set expectations',
            'Lack of focus on reducing waste',
            'Lack of change management successes',
            'Lack of standard practices between sites',
            'Poor inventory control',
          ].map((issue) => (
            <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-error flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-2.5L13.732 4c-.77-.833-1.964-.833-2.732 0L4.082 16.5c-.77.833.192 2.5 1.732 2.5z"/></svg>
              <span class="text-base">{issue}</span>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
        <p class="text-center text-primary font-semibold mt-8 text-lg">
          The good news — all these issues can be addressed with ZoneMaintenance.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Key Quote -->
    <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-neutral text-neutral-content">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
        <QuoteBlock variant="large">
          <p class="text-neutral-content/90">
            "Our maintenance software and methods are designed to eliminate wasted time and effort within Preventative Maintenance (PM) Services — reducing servicing time by over 30% and unplanned breakdowns by over 40%. We provide a defined process to performing effective, repeatable servicing and inspections for mobile mining equipment."
          </p>
        </QuoteBlock>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- iPad Section -->
    <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-base-100">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
        <h2 class="section-heading mb-6">iPad Software</h2>
        <p class="prose-body mb-8">
          Amazing new screens and improved user experience — the iPad software is changing the way maintenance is being executed.
        </p>
        <h3 class="section-subheading mb-4">Creating a Simple Process That's Repeatable and Efficient</h3>
        <p class="prose-body">
          It should be about consistency, not speed. When it comes to mining equipment maintenance, what's important is having a process that can be repeated, time and again, autonomously and always to the same level of accuracy.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Compatible Equipment -->
    <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-base-200">
      <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2 class="section-heading text-center mb-8">Compatible Equipment</h2>
        <p class="prose-body text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-8">
          ZoneMaintenance is ideal for mobile assets, such as:
        </p>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
          {[
            'Off-highway trucks',
            'Large excavators or face shovels',
            'Rope shovels',
            'Motor graders',
            'Track type and wheel dozers',
            'Wheel loaders',
            'Production drills',
            'Underground trucks and loaders',
            'Practically any mobile machine',
          ].map((item) => (
            <div class="card bg-base-100">
              <div class="card-body flex-row items-center gap-3 p-4">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-primary flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4"/></svg>
                <span class="text-base">{item}</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
        <p class="prose-body text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-8">
          ZoneMaintenance is designed to eliminate wasted time and effort within the scheduled PM servicing process of any mobile plant. Plus, it's simple to implement in sites of any size.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Performance Statistics -->
    <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-base-100">
      <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2 class="section-heading text-center mb-4">
          We've Done the Figures, and the Results Are In
        </h2>
        <p class="prose-body text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-12">
          When safety, quality, and effective turnaround is essential, we can help you streamline your maintenance processes for mobile equipment with ZoneMaintenance.
        </p>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-8 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow border-2 border-primary">
            <StatCard value="30%" label="Reduction in PM service times" description="More productivity, more uptime" />
          </div>
          <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow border-2 border-primary">
            <StatCard value="40%" label="Fewer unplanned breakdowns" description="Improved fleet reliability" />
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto mt-8">
          <div class="text-center p-6">
            <p class="text-primary font-bold text-lg mb-1">Save TIME</p>
            <p class="text-base">By increasing uptime</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center p-6">
            <p class="text-primary font-bold text-lg mb-1">Save EFFORT</p>
            <p class="text-base">By reducing labour costs</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center p-6">
            <p class="text-primary font-bold text-lg mb-1">Save MONEY</p>
            <p class="text-base">By improving your bottom line</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Implementation Expectations -->
    <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-base-200">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2 class="section-heading mb-8">What Can You Expect with ZoneMaintenance?</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 prose-body">
          <p>
            Results are entirely dependent on your needs and business requirements. In our experience, substantial site results don't come about from big changes. They happen because the management team is committed to long term improvements and effectively support simple changes to existing workplace habits.
          </p>
          <p>If your company:</p>
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 ml-4 text-base">
            <li>Needs to make a serious adjustment to improve</li>
            <li>This need outweighs any potential resistance to change</li>
            <li>And the change will benefit all levels of your workforce</li>
          </ol>
          <p>
            Then it's entirely possible to quickly achieve <strong class="text-primary">30-40% improvements</strong> across your combined servicing timeframes and a step change in asset reliability. We work closely with your team and communicate with all levels. We take the time to explain what can be achieved and what the system and process are about.
          </p>
          <p>
            The thing that sets ZoneMaintenance apart is its ability to blend with your site environment and requirements seamlessly. It's more than just a flexible software system — it's a methodology that becomes a defined process in itself.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Related Products -->
    <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-base-100">
      <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2 class="section-heading text-center mb-8">Related Product</h2>
        <div class="max-w-xl mx-auto">
          <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow border border-base-300">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h3 class="card-title">RouteMaintenance</h3>
              <div class="badge badge-primary badge-outline">Fixed Plant Maintenance</div>
              <p class="mt-2">
                Focus on efficient, clearly defined, and repeatable methods for carrying out periodic inspections of fixed plant facilities.
              </p>
              <div class="card-actions mt-4">
                <a href="/routemaintenance" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm">
                  Learn More
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3"/></svg>
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <CTABanner
      heading="Looking for a Better System for Your Mining Equipment Maintenance?"
      subtitle="Try our demo version or get in touch to discuss how ZoneMaintenance can transform your operations."
      primaryLabel="Ask for a Demo"
      primaryHref="/contact"
      secondaryLabel="Take Action"
      secondaryHref="/take-action"
    />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
